*bitcoind-0.10.2 (09 Aug 2015)

  09 Aug 2015; Robin H. Johnson <robbat2@gentoo.org> +bitcoind-0.10.2.ebuild,
  +bitcoind-0.10.2-r1.ebuild, +bitcoind-0.11.0.ebuild, +bitcoind-9999.ebuild,
  +files/0.10.0-openrc-compat.patch, +files/0.8-openssl-101k.patch,
  +files/0.8.2-sys_leveldb.patch, +files/0.9-openssl-101k.patch,
  +files/0.9.0-sys_leveldb.patch, +files/0.9.x-ljr_noblacklist.patch,
  +files/9999-syslibs.patch, +files/bitcoin.conf, +files/bitcoin.confd,
  +files/bitcoin.initd-r1, +files/bitcoind.logrotate,
  +files/bitcoind.logrotate-r1, +files/bitcoind.service, +metadata.xml:
  proj/gentoo: Initial commit

  This commit represents a new era for Gentoo:
  Storing the gentoo-x86 tree in Git, as converted from CVS.

  This commit is the start of the NEW history.
  Any historical data is intended to be grafted onto this point.

  Creation process:
  1. Take final CVS checkout snapshot
  2. Remove ALL ChangeLog* files
  3. Transform all Manifests to thin
  4. Remove empty Manifests
  5. Convert all stale $Header$/$Id$ CVS keywords to non-expanded Git $Id$
  5.1. Do not touch files with -kb/-ko keyword flags.

  Signed-off-by: Robin H. Johnson <robbat2@gentoo.org>
